arped\ndisk with specific angular momentum $\\sim 3$ times larger than the specific\nangular momentum of the galaxy halo. Such warped disks are common features in\nhydrodynamical simulations of cold-flow accretion onto galaxies; the data\npresented here provide observational evidence in favour of this scenario.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Oct 2017 17:27:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-20"}
